sql:
SELECT o.IdOrder
FROM Orders o
JOIN Books_Order bo1 ON o.IdOrder = bo1.IdOrder
JOIN Book b1 ON bo1.ISBN = b1.ISBN
JOIN Books_Order bo2 ON o.IdOrder = bo2.IdOrder
JOIN Book b2 ON bo2.ISBN = b2.ISBN
WHERE b1.Title = 'Pride and Prejudice'
  AND b2.Title = 'The Little Prince'
GROUP BY o.IdOrder;
question: Show ids for orders including both "Pride and Prejudice" and "The Little Prince".

sql:
SELECT IdOrder
FROM Books_Order
WHERE ISBN IN (
    SELECT ISBN FROM Book WHERE Title = 'Pride and Prejudice'
)
INTERSECT
SELECT IdOrder
FROM Books_Order
WHERE ISBN IN (
    SELECT ISBN FROM Book WHERE Title = 'The Little Prince'
);

sql:
SELECT IdOrder
FROM Books_Order
JOIN Book ON Books_Order.ISBN = Book.ISBN
WHERE Book.Title IN ('Pride and Prejudice', 'The Little Prince')
GROUP BY IdOrder
HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT Book.Title) = 2;
